Digital Video & Audio Studio      35 West 4th Street, 2nd Floor     212-998-3500      Map >>         Regular Semester Hours      Mon-Thurs: 9:00am-9:00pm     Fri: 9:00am-5:00pm       Sat-Sun: noon-8:00pm               did you know?      The ITS Advanced Media Studio is     also located at 35 West 4th Street, 2nd Floor, but     is a separate facility.       related pages            Software packages available for use at ITS labs       Technology resources available at ITS labs              Access Policy   This center's resources are open to all NYU students in degree and diploma programs, faculty and staff, and Lab Access Account holders. For information about obtaining such an account, visit the ITS Accounts section.    Computer Platforms Available   Macintosh    General Resources     Internet access   Web browsers   The Microsoft Office Suite   Laser printing   Lab staff to assist students in the basics of using an ITS student lab and  other ITS resources such as NYU Classes and NYUHome      Specialized Resources     Flatbed scanners equipped with film adapters (positive and negative)   Audio, video, and image editing   Web and print publishing   3 video editing stations and transfers between VHS, mini-DV and DVCAM    6 video editing systems for short quality video pieces using the mini-DV standard and Apple's   FinalCutPro or Avid editing software    3 ProTools audio systems with Roland MIDI keyboards    High quality scanning of positive and negative film and reflective film    Printing on medium format archival & non-archival printers   2 video editing booths for advanced students and faculty working on larger video post-production projects. Primarily used to edit analog Betacam SP source materials, in addition to mini-DV, DVCAM, and DVC-Pro digital formats   Large format printing with archival and non-archival output   Live Audio Production Suite      Note : Specialized resources (video, audio, assistive technologies) are available by in-person request. Please stop by the Center to schedule a reservation.    For a complete list of the software applications, hardware, peripherals, and other equipment available at each ITS lab location, see Software packages available for use at ITS labs and Technology resources available at ITS labs .    Supported Media   CD-R, CD-RW, and USB and Firewire devices (general); DVD-R, CD-RW, mini-DV, DVCAM, and DAT. Video dubbing rack format: DVCAM, Betacam SP, Hi-8, S-VHS, VHS, mini-DV (specialized).    Live Audio Production Suite   The Fourth Street Academic Technology Center also houses a Live Audio Production Suite equipped for video and audio production and post-production. Hours are the same as the Fourth Street Academic Technology Center hours (above), and the resources are available on a first come, first served basis.    Page last reviewed: February 17, 2015
